    {
        "content": "<p>Don't we already have type erasure approach for fences?</p>",
        "id": 582187005,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1774621952
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's one fence that the driver owns and can signal, that one is not type erased.</p>",
        "id": 582187051,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1774621966
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Then there's a separate type that can be used to react to signals, which is type erased.</p>",
        "id": 582187106,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1774621977
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's the design I was told about.</p>",
        "id": 582187119,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1774621980
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah right, <code>Fence</code> data is uniquely owned by the signaler, so this is probably not needed. Anyway, could be useful for some other usecases where you need to stuff <code>Arc&lt;dyn Trait&gt;</code> or something similar to XArray.</p>",
        "id": 582189941,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1774622679
    }
]